This paper discusses the usage and impact of user-generated media, such as Facebook, LinkedIn, and Twitter, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the issue of information overload, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and social media analysis (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper touches upon the topic of privacy, which is relevant to the sub-category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social network analysis (cs.SD).
